  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Ninjutsu (Doton)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 8 (Spell Level 4)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 10</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 22 | <b>Successes:</b> 3</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 10 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 23</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, H</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You must be in contact with the surface you wish to affect, or one directly connected to it. You send your Chakra into the roof of a cave or tunnel or the side of a cliff and cause it to collapse. Creatures caught by the collapsing earth take 5d8 earth damage and must make a Reflex save to avoid becoming @Condition[pinned]{pinned} beneath the rubble.<br><br>A creature that is pinned beneath rubble takes 1d6 nonlethal damage every minute, increasing by 1d6 every time (2d6 the second minute, etc). If they fall unconscious, they must make a Constitution check (DC 15) each round to avoid taking 1d4 damage.<br><br>If the area does not have a cliff face or roof, the technique only produces a brief earthquake, causing crea- tures to fall @Condition[prone]{prone} unless they succeed at a Reflex save (DC 15).</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
